<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,1622,1706]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,1622,1644]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">FIGURE 25.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ramme" authorityYear="1933" box="[295,424,1624,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicornis">
<emphasis box="[295,424,1624,1645]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">P. varicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A, D, male; B, E, female; C, pronotum of male in profile; F, male cerci from above; G, male cerci and subgenital plate; H, ovipositor (leg. R. Ebner in 1928 from Lebanon. Photos credit by Harald Bruckenr, Naturhistorisches Museum Wien, Austria).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1745,2022]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1745,1770]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Female:</emphasis>
Fastigium as in male (
<figureCitation box="[555,661,1745,1770]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1778,1800]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1757]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,193,1757]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 22. Dorsal view of pronotum. A–B, P. salmani sp. n. (male); C, P. zonatus datca ssp. n. (male); D, P. variicercis (male); E–F, P. salmani sp. n. (female); G, P. zonatus datca (male); I, P. variicercis (female); J–K, P. varicornis (male and female, not in scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242375/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 22K</figureCitation>
). Pronotum selliform, constricted at mesozona with slightly concave caudal margin (
<figureCitation box="[324,438,1781,1806]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1778,1800]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1757]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,193,1757]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 22. Dorsal view of pronotum. A–B, P. salmani sp. n. (male); C, P. zonatus datca ssp. n. (male); D, P. variicercis (male); E–F, P. salmani sp. n. (female); G, P. zonatus datca (male); I, P. variicercis (female); J–K, P. varicornis (male and female, not in scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242375/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs. 22K</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[449,498,1781,1806]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,202,1574]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1601]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 25. P. varicornis. A, D, male; B, E, female; C, pronotum of male in profile; F, male cerci from above; G, male cerci and subgenital plate; H, ovipositor (leg. R. Ebner in 1928 from Lebanon. Photos credit by Harald Bruckenr, Naturhistorisches Museum Wien, Austria)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242381/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">25E</figureCitation>
). In profile, pronotum slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[947,1050,1781,1806]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,202,1574]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1601]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 25. P. varicornis. A, D, male; B, E, female; C, pronotum of male in profile; F, male cerci from above; G, male cerci and subgenital plate; H, ovipositor (leg. R. Ebner in 1928 from Lebanon. Photos credit by Harald Bruckenr, Naturhistorisches Museum Wien, Austria)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242381/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 25B</figureCitation>
). Tegmina visible, but shorter than half of pronota, apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[498,599,1817,1842]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,202,1574]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1601]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 25. P. varicornis. A, D, male; B, E, female; C, pronotum of male in profile; F, male cerci from above; G, male cerci and subgenital plate; H, ovipositor (leg. R. Ebner in 1928 from Lebanon. Photos credit by Harald Bruckenr, Naturhistorisches Museum Wien, Austria)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242381/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 25E</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor, gonangulum and lamella as in 
<figureCitation box="[1095,1198,1817,1842]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,202,1574]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1601]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 25. P. varicornis. A, D, male; B, E, female; C, pronotum of male in profile; F, male cerci from above; G, male cerci and subgenital plate; H, ovipositor (leg. R. Ebner in 1928 from Lebanon. Photos credit by Harald Bruckenr, Naturhistorisches Museum Wien, Austria)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242381/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 25H</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1745,2022]" lastBlockId="35.[151,1437,151,392]" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1853,1878]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ramme" authorityYear="1933" box="[327,472,1854,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicornis">
<emphasis box="[327,472,1854,1877]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">P. varicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ramme" authorityYear="1933" box="[686,1003,1853,1878]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicornis" subGenus="Ephippigera">
<emphasis box="[686,1003,1853,1878]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">L. (Ephippigera) varicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1077,1179,1853,1878]" name="Lebanon" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
. Fontana and Buzzetti (2004), who reported some information on the taxonomic story, examined the examples which were collected by R. Ebner from 
<collectingCountry box="[291,389,1925,1950]" name="Lebanon" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
(diagnosed by W. Ramme). They have reported that the distribution of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ramme" authorityYear="1933" box="[1263,1408,1926,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicornis">
<emphasis box="[1263,1408,1926,1949]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">P. varicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is limited to 
<collectingCountry box="[273,375,1961,1986]" name="Lebanon" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
. A database (http://www.biologie.uni-ulm.de/systax/) and OSF contain some pictures of the museum samples, diagnosed as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ramme" authorityYear="1933" box="[518,663,1998,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicornis">
<emphasis box="[518,663,1998,2021]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">P. varicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by W. Ramme which were collected from Fethiye, Göçek (
<collectingRegion box="[1354,1431,1997,2022]" country="Turkey" name="Mugla" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Muğla</collectingRegion>
, TR) deposited in 
<collectingRegion box="[350,455,151,176]" country="Germany" name="Hamburg" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Hamburg</collectingRegion>
Museum (
<collectionCode box="[579,668,152,176]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/82c5-17ij" name="Zoologisches Institut und Zoologisches Museum, Universitat Hamburg" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">ZMUH</collectionCode>
). However, W. Ramme did not publish any information about these specimens. According to the data obtained from the fresh materials, collected in this area, it became clear that the population distributed around 
<collectingRegion box="[491,564,223,248]" country="Turkey" name="Mugla" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Muğla</collectingRegion>
was not 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ramme" authorityYear="1933" box="[667,810,225,248]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicornis">
<emphasis box="[667,810,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">P. varicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Along with the previous specimens from this area, the population is given as a new species in this study (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sevgili &amp; Şirin &amp; Heller &amp; Lemonnier-Darcemont" authorityYear="2018" box="[717,833,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salmani">
<emphasis box="[717,833,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">P. salmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
This species has not been assessed for the 
<collectionCode box="[691,759,296,320]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">IUCN</collectionCode>
Red List (2017–3). There is also not enough data about 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ramme" authorityYear="1933" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicornis">P. varicornis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and it was not possible to consider it on the basis of the extent of occurrence criteries of 
<collectionCode box="[1286,1354,332,356]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">IUCN</collectionCode>
(DD = data deficient).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
